 Slowdown:** Trace1 pays for extra launches and intermediate traffic between sorting, staged expert work, and the final reduction. Trace2 completes the same logical block in one kernel, which reduces launch overhead relative to the decomposed path.\n\n**Resolution:** Fusing the mixture-of-experts stages keeps intermediate state resident across fewer synchronization points and matches the proven single-kernel structure seen on trace2 for this workload shape.\n\n**Impact estimate:**\n\n- Low end (75% gap target): 0.270 ms savings (21.43% E2E)\n- High end (100% gap target): 0.360 ms savings (28.57% E2E)\n- Fusion pattern: memory-bound, memory_bound\n- Confidence: Medium — kernel-count split and measured gap are clear; candidate typing data is coarse for some kernels\n\n## Impact Summary\n\n| Recommendation | Type | Estimated Savings (ms) | Estimated Improvement (E2E %) | Confidence |\n|----------------|------|----------------------|-------------------------------|------------|\n| MoE fused path for moe_layer | kernel_fusion | 0.27–0.36 (mid 0.315) | 21.43–28.57 | Medium |\n","message":"The file /home/AMD/khoffmey/dev/TraceLens/evals/unit_tests_comparative/test01_moe_fused_vs_unfused/analysis_output_ref/system_findings/kernel_fusion_findings.md has been updated."}}}}},{"toolCall":{"shellToolCall":{"args":{"command":"cd /home/AMD/khoffmey/dev/TraceLens && python3 -c \"\nimport sys\nfrom TraceLens.AgenticMode.Standalone.utils.validation_utils import validate_findings_file\npassed, errors = validate_findings_file(sys.argv[1], sys.argv[2])\nif not passed:\n    for e in errors:\n        print('  - ' + e)\n    sys.exit(1)\n\" '/home/AMD/khoffmey/dev/TraceLens/evals/unit_tests_comparative/test01_moe_fused_vs_unfused/analysis_output_ref/system_findings/kernel_fusion_findings.md' 'system'","workingDirectory":"","timeout":30000,"toolCallId":"tool_ba3d36fd-438b-40ac-b97b-22fa1fd1fce","simpleCommands":["cd","python3"],"hasInputRedirect":false,"hasOutputRedirect":false,"parsingResul